  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "<!-- Please only use this template for submitting enhancement requests -->\r\n\r\n**What would you like to be added**:\r\nApply security best practices for both kube-dns and core-dns.\r\n\r\n### kube-dns\r\nLow hanging fruit:\r\n\r\n- [x]  Run as non-root & disallow privilege escalation\r\n- [x] Run with the default seccomp profile (i.e.  `runtime/default`)\r\n- [x] ReadOnlyRootFilesystem\r\n- [x] Avoid unnecessary HostPath volumes\r\n- [x]  ~~Don't mount service account token~~ (n/a)\r\n\r\nMore advanced:\r\n\r\n- [ ] Reduce dependencies in the base image (#40248)\r\n- [ ] Custom seccomp profile\r\n- [ ] Custom AppArmor profile\r\n- [x] Drop unneeded capabilities\r\n\r\n### core-dns\r\n- [x]  Run as non-root & disallow privilege escalation\r\n- [x] Run with the default seccomp profile (i.e.  `runtime/default`)\r\n- [x] ReadOnlyRootFilesystem\r\n- [x] Avoid unnecessary HostPath volumes\r\n- [x]  ~~Don't mount service account token~~ (n/a)\r\n\r\nMore advanced:\r\n\r\n- [ ] Reduce dependencies in the base image (#40248)\r\n- [ ] Custom seccomp profile\r\n- [ ] Custom AppArmor profile\r\n- [x] Drop unneeded capabilities\r\n\r\nThis is based on the long term issue #38541 and implemented by PR #82347.\r\n\r\n**Why is this needed**:\r\nOur system pods should run using security best practices, both to enhance cluster security and serve as examples of best practices to users.",
